## 🎨 Styling Rules (styled-components)

### ✅ Always Use styled-components for Styling

- **Never** use inline `style` props
- **Never** use `StyleSheet.create()`
- All styling must be done via `styled-components/native`

```ts
import styled from "styled-components/native";
```

### ✅ Basic Component Styling

❌ **Bad:**

```tsx
<View style={{ flex: 1, backgroundColor: "#fff", padding: 16 }}>
  <Text style={{ fontSize: 18, fontWeight: "bold", color: "#333" }}>Hello</Text>
</View>
```

✅ **Good:**

```tsx
const Container = styled.View`
  flex: 1;
  background-color: #fff;
  padding: 16px;
`

const Title = styled.Text`
  font-size: 18px;
  font-weight: bold;
  color: #333;
`

// Usage
<Container>
  <Title>Hello</Title>
</Container>
```

### ✅ Use Theme for Design Tokens

Define a global theme and never hardcode colors, spacing, or typography values:

```ts
// lib/theme.ts
export const theme = {
  colors: {
    primary: "#6200EE",
    background: "#FFFFFF",
    surface: "#F5F5F5",
    text: "#333333",
    error: "#B00020",
  },
  spacing: {
    xs: "4px",
    sm: "8px",
    md: "16px",
    lg: "24px",
    xl: "32px",
  },
  typography: {
    body: "14px",
    subtitle: "16px",
    title: "20px",
    heading: "28px",
  },
  radii: {
    sm: "4px",
    md: "8px",
    lg: "16px",
    full: "9999px",
  },
} as const;

export type AppTheme = typeof theme;
```

### ✅ Wrap App with ThemeProvider

```tsx
// app/_layout.tsx
import { ThemeProvider } from "styled-components/native";
import { theme } from "@/lib/theme";

export default function RootLayout() {
  return (
    <ThemeProvider theme={theme}>
      <Stack />
    </ThemeProvider>
  );
}
```

### ✅ Access Theme Inside Styled Components

```tsx
const Button = styled.TouchableOpacity`
  background-color: ${({ theme }) => theme.colors.primary};
  padding: ${({ theme }) => theme.spacing.md};
  border-radius: ${({ theme }) => theme.radii.md};
`;

const ButtonText = styled.Text`
  color: #fff;
  font-size: ${({ theme }) => theme.typography.subtitle};
  font-weight: bold;
`;
```

### ✅ Use Props for Variants

❌ **Bad:** Creating multiple separate styled components for variants

```tsx
const PrimaryButton = styled.TouchableOpacity`...`;
const SecondaryButton = styled.TouchableOpacity`...`;
```

✅ **Good:** Use props to handle variants

```tsx
type ButtonProps = {
  variant?: "primary" | "secondary" | "ghost";
};

const StyledButton = styled.TouchableOpacity<ButtonProps>`
  background-color: ${({ theme, variant }) =>
    variant === "secondary"
      ? theme.colors.surface
      : variant === "ghost"
        ? "transparent"
        : theme.colors.primary};
  padding: ${({ theme }) => theme.spacing.md};
  border-radius: ${({ theme }) => theme.radii.md};
`;
```

### ✅ Extend Existing Styled Components

```tsx
const BaseCard = styled.View`
  background-color: ${({ theme }) => theme.colors.surface};
  border-radius: ${({ theme }) => theme.radii.lg};
  padding: ${({ theme }) => theme.spacing.md};
`;

const ElevatedCard = styled(BaseCard)`
  shadow-color: #000;
  shadow-offset: 0px 2px;
  shadow-opacity: 0.1;
  shadow-radius: 4px;
  elevation: 3;
`;
```

### ✅ Typed Theme with TypeScript

Augment the DefaultTheme to get full autocomplete:

```ts
// types/styled.d.ts
import "styled-components/native";
import { AppTheme } from "@/lib/theme";

declare module "styled-components/native" {
  export interface DefaultTheme extends AppTheme {}
}
```

### ✅ Co-locate Styled Components

Keep styled components in the same file as the component unless they are shared:

```
features/
  auth/
    components/
      LoginForm.tsx        ← styled components defined here
      LoginForm.styles.ts  ← only extract if file gets too large (200+ lines)
```

### ✅ Naming Conventions

- Prefix styled components with `Styled` only if it helps avoid name conflicts
- Otherwise, use clear semantic names: `Container`, `Title`, `Card`, `Row`, `Wrapper`
- Never name a styled component the same as a React Native primitive (e.g., don't name it `View` or `Text`)

```tsx
// ✅ Good names
const Container = styled.View`...`;
const HeroTitle = styled.Text`...`;
const ActionRow = styled.View`...`;

// ❌ Avoid
const View = styled.View`...`;
const StyledStyledButton = styled.TouchableOpacity`...`;
```

### ✅ Dark Mode Support

Use theme switching via Zustand + ThemeProvider:

```ts
// store/themeStore.ts
import { create } from "zustand";
import { lightTheme, darkTheme } from "@/lib/theme";

type ThemeStore = {
  isDark: boolean;
  theme: typeof lightTheme;
  toggleTheme: () => void;
};

export const useThemeStore = create<ThemeStore>((set) => ({
  isDark: false,
  theme: lightTheme,
  toggleTheme: () =>
    set((state) => ({
      isDark: !state.isDark,
      theme: state.isDark ? lightTheme : darkTheme,
    })),
}));
```

```tsx
// app/_layout.tsx
const theme = useThemeStore((state) => state.theme);

return (
  <ThemeProvider theme={theme}>
    <Stack />
  </ThemeProvider>
);
```

