## 🎯 Final Golden Rules

- Always prefer type safety over speed
- Never use `any`
- Always separate API logic from UI
- Always validate forms with Zod
- Use TanStack Query for server state
- Use Zustand only for client/global state
- Avoid side effects inside components
- Keep components small and composable
- Never use inline styles or `StyleSheet.create()` — always use styled-components
- Always use theme tokens for colors, spacing, and typography — never hardcode values
- If unsure, choose the more scalable architecture
- Use Expo (SDK, expo CLI, config plugins, dev client, etc.), but do not use Expo Application Services (EAS)—no eas build, eas submit, EAS Update, or EAS-only env/build flows. Prefer local builds (Xcode, Android Studio / Gradle, npx expo prebuild + native projects, or your own CI).
